@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam maxMessageSize 150

' 1. Define the Client
class Client {
}

' 2. Define the Subject interface
interface Subject <<interface>> {
  + request()
}

' 3. Define the RealSubject (The object doing the actual work)
class RealSubject {
  + request()
}

' 4. Define the Proxy 
class Proxy {
  - realSubject: RealSubject
  + request()
}

' Relationships
Client -right-> Subject : " Uses >"
Subject <|.. RealSubject : " Implements"
Subject <|.. Proxy : " Implements"

' The Proxy holds a reference to the RealSubject via Composition
Proxy o-right-> RealSubject : " Maintains reference to >"

' Notes for Logic Explanation
note top of Subject
  **Subject**
  Defines the common interface for 
  both RealSubject and Proxy.
end note

note bottom of Proxy
  **Proxy::request()** internal implementation:
  
  ""if (realSubject == null) {""
  ""    // Lazy initialization (Virtual Proxy)""
  ""    realSubject = new RealSubject();""
  ""}""
  ""// Perform access control, networking, etc.""
  ""realSubject.request();""
end note

note bottom of RealSubject
  **RealSubject**
  The real object that the proxy 
  represents and controls access to.
end note

@enduml
